2. In your activity or fragment, create a Composable that requests the background location permission:

```
@Composable
fun BackgroundLocationPermissionRequester(
    onPermissionGranted: () -> Unit,
    onPermissionDenied: () -> Unit,
    onCancelPermissionRequest: () -> Unit,
) {
    val context = LocalContext.current
    val backgroundLocationPermissionState = rememberPermissionState(
        android.Manifest.permission.ACCESS_BACKGROUND_LOCATION
    )

    val shouldShowBackgroundLocationRationale = backgroundLocationPermissionState.shouldShowRationale

    PermissionRequested(
        permissionState = backgroundLocationPermissionState,
        permissionNotAvailableContent = {
            Toast.makeText(
                context,
                "Background location permission is not available",
                Toast.LENGTH_SHORT
            ).show()

            onPermissionDenied()
        },
        permissionNotGrantedContent = {
            Column(modifier = Modifier.fillMaxSize()) {
                Text(text = "Location permission is required for this feature")
                Spacer(modifier = Modifier.height(8.dp))

                Button(
                    onClick = {
                        backgroundLocationPermissionState.launchPermissionRequest()
                    }
                ) {
                    Text(text = "Request permission")
                }
            }
        },
        permissionGrantedContent = {
            onPermissionGranted()
        },
        shouldShowRationaleContent = {
            Column(modifier = Modifier.fillMaxSize()) {
                Text(text = "Location permission is required to use this feature")
                Spacer(modifier = Modifier.height(8.dp))
                Button(
                    onClick = backgroundLocationPermissionState::launchPermissionRequest
                ) {
                    Text(text = "Request permission")
                }
                Spacer(modifier = Modifier.height(8.dp))
                Button(onClick = onCancelPermissionRequest) {
                    Text(text = "Cancel")
                }
            }
        }
    )
}
```

In this example, we are using the `rememberPermissionState` function to create a `PermissionState` object for the `ACCESS_BACKGROUND_LOCATION` permission. We use this object to check the status of the permission and request it when necessary.

The `PermissionRequested` composable is used to display different UI based on the status of the permission. This composable displays a message to the user, along with a button to request permission.

3. In your activity, call the `BackgroundLocationPermissionRequester` composable to request the permission:

```
